<br>
Skalds:Excellent balance, could use something of a dot effect but in all reality the instant mez shout is continually an annoyance to other realms.<br>
<br>
Thanes:Again, well balanced class. A few Thanes and aoe spells are a good thing to clean house.<br>
<br>
Berserkers:Well, they were recently nerfed a bit and range wise they are screwed. RvR is pretty much a ranged players paradise. If they do manage to get close to you however, send your regards to Broadway because you aren;t going to be seeing it anytime soon.<br>
<br>
Warriors: See Berserker but with better armor/defense<br>
<br>
Runies:Not enough of them. That is all.<br>
<br>
Spiritmasters: See Runies. Multiply by the fact that most of them are pet-heavy. Awesome for suppression and defence though.<br>
<br>
Healers:NOT ENOUGH, I can't put it any other way. Plus, Albion has better instant heals.<br>
<br>
Shaman:A travesty. I started as a Shaman when I first started playing DAoC. Slightly more soloable then healers. Must spec away from healing to be effective in RvR (IE Cave Magic) and until recently, still horribly underpowered in cave magic. I haven't checked with the guy I gave my shaman to when I left DAoC the first time, but he quit playing for a while due to how bad they were in RvR. I don't know what his take would be on the new shaman mods to cave magic.<br>
<br>
Shadowblades:Good amount, high damage. Uber.<br>
<br>
Hunter:Has to spec away from pets to be very effective in RvR. You have a choice with this class. Be awesome in RvR or be awesome in PvE. Their is no middle ground. Spec high in bow and stealth, neglecting the spear specs and pet specs, and you will do well in RvR. You will have horrible solobility, and many groups will not invite you because you don't contribute as much, but you will own in RvR.<br>
<br>
The biggest issue?<br>
<br>
Albion has 3 healing classes. They have better instant heals. Midgard can, with balanced attack, still have their way with them but in many cases the healing is just not there. <br>
<br>
Due to the extra healing class, Albion can 'zerg' much more effectively. They have the healing power to avoid true strategy. Melee-wise, they don't match up. However, when you have two albs for every one middie, well you get my drift.<br>
<br>
You notice I leave Hibernia out of this. This would be because, on a class to class basis, Hibernia is the red-headed stepchild of Albion/Midgard. They simply can't effectively match up. In fact, in many cases they don't even attempt to RvR. Never hardly see them on Palomides and on my friend's server (Tristan) they are getting their ass smoked. They are basically a PvE realm and require massive balance. <br>
<br>
Anyway, thats my state of the game take.<br>
<br>
